cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.GR 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with feature matching and pose estimation in real-world environments using neural networks. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper uses end-to-end training to learn priors over geometric transformations and regularities of the 3D world. 
3. cs.RO (Robotics) is a possible category as the paper mentions the integration of the proposed method into modern SLAM systems. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper uses neural networks to solve the optimal transport problem and aggregate context information. 
5. cs.GR (Graphics) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with 3D scene understanding and feature assignments.
